Toronto, ONBusiness Analyst – Toronto, ON

Corporate IT within CBI Health Group plays a key role in ensuring that we have the application systems in place to enable all end users – from care providers to support staff – to perform their duties effectively and, ultimately, ensure the delivery of excellent patient care.

As a Business Analyst, based in our IT Corporate Office, you will ensure that proper requirements are gathered from key stakeholders in operations, and translate these into application design and mockups representing potential application solutions. This role is invaluable in ensuring that what we are developing in Applications will meet key stakeholders’ needs in the end, and that there is continued communication and consensus through the whole process. You will also help ensure the sustainability of the use of the new solution, and support operations in ensuring compliance through successful change management. Among your priorities will be reviewing and understanding current application systems and processes, documenting recent changes, and gathering, analyzing and documenting business requirements for CBI’s application development initiatives related to new Rehab Clinic Network and Home Health's new feature sets planned for upcoming releases. As a source of expertise and support for facility end-users, you will aid them on-site during, pre- and post-implementation of the new feature sets, update living documents to understand issues that arise, and aid in prioritizing issues, finding creative 'work-arounds' for less urgent issues, as well as identifying and documenting those requiring developmental priority in a patch release.

PRIMARY DUTIES
As a Business Analyst, you will:
Define, analyze and document business requirements in the form of process workflows, DFDs, BRDs, and tracking the ongoing changes of these documents
Perform activities to better understand the constantly changing needs of the business, and assess the impact of those changes
Support the communication and delivery of requirements through the complete system development life cycle (SDLC) with the relevant stakeholders
Act as the key liaison between the business and IT for the assigned projects
Ensure that requests align with the organization’s strategic goals and escalate, as needed, to the Product Managers and Owners if you see discrepancies in the requested changes.

QUALIFICATIONS
To take on the role of Business Analyst, you must have:
Experience using various techniques for eliciting requirements;
Understanding of project lifecycle and project approaches;
Understanding of project definition and scoping principles;
Experience with, and ability to be flexible filling, various roles throughout the project lifecycle;
Experience documenting business, functional and non-functional stakeholder requirements as well as the tools (Visio, Word, other MS applications) and methodologies (DFD, data modelling techniques, Use Cases) used;
Experience with, and understanding of, change control processes in relation to requirements documentation;
Ability to effectively identify and document project risks, issues, assumptions and dependencies;
Experience using various requirement prioritizing techniques;
Experience using application mockup tools such as Pencil, protoshare, Balsamiq, Adobe;
Proven ability to work well in a team, having experience working with QAs, Developers, and Project Managers;
Team Lead experience would be an asset for a potential move to Senior BA role.

Levio specializes in the implementation of major programs or projects related to organizational transformation. Our firm brings together top-caliber experienced consultants whose expertise enables them to master the most complex issues throughout the lifecycle of a transformation program or project. Our services cover strategic consulting, program management, project management, business architecture and business process reengineering, functional, organizational and technological architecture of information systems, implementation of technical business solution and field support in setting up processes up to the collection of inherent benefits.

Our interventions are based on:

Concrete commitment to deliver the expected benefits;
Succeed as a team, through work, leadership and adaptability;
The highest degree of rigor in planning, monitoring and execution;
Sense of responsibility;
Pride and enthusiasm for our customers' success.

The position:
Our business analysts work with various stakeholders to collect, analyze, communicate and validate requirements in projects. You will offer solutions that enable the organization to achieve its objectives.


Defines business needs, analyzes them and proposes a business solution to meet them;
Describes existing business processes, identifies gaps between current and target processes to support the proposed business solution;
Ensure compliance with business and user needs;
Participate in the various stages of testing and simulation in order to achieve full compliance of the converted data;
Participate in change management and support the training team;
Act as an intermediary between business and technical teams and define technical and operational requirements;
Communicate with project managers, subject matter experts and business architects.

Here's how to impress us:

Bachelor's degree in related field (BBA);
Experience working as a business analyst (5 to 9 years);
Experience in consultation (preferred);
Experience with multidisciplinary and multi-site teams (preferred);
Rigorous, results-oriented person with proven ability to meet schedule, budget and scope of project;
Excellent ability to influence and communicate;
Leadership, customer-oriented, strong propensity for teamwork;
Ability to manage team communications, problem solving and stakeholder relationships;
Ability to work in complex environments.

Our organization offers a stimulating environment, a fertile ground to advance your career by enhancing and applying your skills and know-how. We promote a coaching approach to optimize the knowledge and competency of each member. Each employee has access to a dedicated yearly fund for professional development to help them reach their full potential. We also offer a large package of fringe benefits.

We are looking for people with personality, action people for whom IT is a passion.

Toronto, ONPosition:

Senior Business Analyst


Reports To:

Senior Manager, Business Analysis


Tier:

Staff


Department:

Product Management


Company:

GS1 Canada


Location:
Toronto


Status:

Full time, Contract


Job Number:

1422


Key Role
The Senior Business Analyst works on a diverse and broad spectrum of significant- to-moderate complexity projects to define and design comprehensive business solutions in response to business priorities and stakeholder requirements. This role will require a combination of skills including Business Analysis and most importantly – a consultative approach to working with our business stakeholders. You will need to have a strong work ethic, a positive attitude and the ability to listen, allowing you to efficiently decipher business needs.

Duties and Responsibilities
Assess, research, analyse and document sponsor/stakeholder requirements in accordance with project life cycle methodologies being utilized, and including standard reporting tools, requirements gathering methodologies, process models, data analysis, GUI/report designs, demos and prototypes;
Facilitate requirements elicitation with business stakeholders;
Recommend business solutions that satisfy sponsor/stakeholder needs continually exploring and assessing options for enhanced value to our subscribers;
Define and execute UAT plans while ensuring acceptance criteria is satisfied;
Provide support, leadership and expertise for the requirements definition, design, testing and implementation of GS1 CA products and services through demonstration of working knowledge of SDLC and Agile Methodologies;
Prepare end-user documentation and training material;
Resolve conflict/issues using different tactics prior to escalation;
Understand all business systems within GS1 Canada to perform proper impact assessments;
Conduct workshops, demos and pilots with internal stakeholders and the subscriber community;
Work closely with the project manager to monitor and ensure that the project is being accurately tracked;
Support industry committees with functional expertise on business systems;
Present analysis, requirements and findings to management and internal/external stakeholders to communicate systems/business capabilities and recommendations;
Required Knowledge, Skills, and Experience

Post-secondary degree, preferably in Business or Information Technology;
Certified Business Analysis Professional (CBAP) or similar IIBA certification;
Minimum of 5 years’ experience in Retail, Manufacturing and/or Supply Chain industries in the capacity of business analysis and system design;
Demonstrated experience in defining and documenting business requirements;
Demonstrated experience in use case and business process modeling;
Demonstrated experience in development and execution of User Acceptance Testing (UAT) Plans;
Working knowledge of project management methodologies;
Strong facilitation skills to gather and document requirements;
Proven experience supporting multiple projects with competing priorities and strict deadlines;
Proven ability to build effective and successful relationships within and outside the organization;
Ability to work at a detailed level and quickly learn business application-specific details;
Strong orientation toward excellence in results and proven ability to quickly become a subject matter expert;
Communicates complex issues in a clear and understandable manner to others and proven presentation skills;
Capable of applying a professional knowledge, possessing a high level of problem solving, analytical abilities and negotiation skills;
Proven high level of proficiency with MS Office suite (Word, Excel & PowerPoint, etc);

