Burnaby, BCEncepta is a young, growing company, looking for people to help build our future in areas of engineering, software, data collection, and business development. Our mission is to build a company that combines great service with innovative technology and data to improve how utilities manage and enhance their distributed assets, to provide better communications, energy and transportation for their customers. By working together, our company is a place where personal growth is valued and we are free to live the lives we want to lead.

We’re looking for people who:
Are Curious, think about the big picture, and create innovative solutions
Take Pride in producing quality work and take initiative to improve
Work Together with our clients and ourselves to understand their needs and build lasting relationships
Get It Done by working through challenges without losing sight of the end goal
Do The Right Thing by showing integrity and compassion to our people, clients, and communities
We currently have an opportunity for a Project Manager/Business Analyst. In this role you will have the opportunity to work as part of a multidisciplinary team that is reshaping the telecommunications and utilities industries. Some of the responsibilities include:

Engaging business users to identify problems and challenges and to define and prioritize business requirements;
Proposing creative and effective solutions to solve challenges; solutions may take the form of business process improvements, IT, data or organizational;
Evaluating business cases for potential projects to assess and evaluate economic and practical feasibility;
Executing tasks throughout the project lifecycle including such tasks as data analysis, business requirements definition, functional designs, technical specification creation, test preparation and execution, user training and go-live support;
Assisting in the definition of roadmaps and IT strategy to define a forward investment path for our products and IT solutions;
Supporting business development activities to help understand customer requirements, develop solutions, run pilot projects and to help support new types of work;
Providing coaching to others to help the team effectively deliver projects.
Some travel maybe required; and,
Other duties as requested by manager.
Our ideal candidate:

Has proven skills in business analysis - definition of business requirements, development of business cases, development of functional designs, functional testing;
Has substantial experience of delivering projects over their life cycle - analysis, design, build, test, go-live;
Is experienced in liaising with technical teams include software teams for the delivery of projects, and experience acting as an intermediary between business users and developers;
Is knowledgeable in project delivery methodology (e.g. agile, waterfall);
Has a proven record of managing or supporting management in the delivery of projects; a PMI certification would be an asset;
Can demonstrate strong problem solving skills;
Has client-facing experience; strong customer service ethos and relationship building skills (either in consultancy or with internal stakeholders);
Has some experience leading a small team, coaching and mentoring others;
Has knowledge and experience in telecommunications infrastructure, power distribution infrastructure, underground utilities or in other engineering disciplines;
Is skilled and experienced in data analysis and visualization.
We want our employees to succeed in everything they do! We provide professional development and learning opportunities, a relaxed, collaborative atmosphere with a great group of people and snacks! Some of our other awesome benefits include vacation, paid sick time and paid flex days and an Active Lifestyle spending account to to ensure a healthy work life balance. We also offer RRSP matching and a generous health and dental plan.

