$69,290 a yearPermanentThe Municipal Property Assessment Corporation, Information Quality and Support Services branch of the Information Technology department requires a Technology Infrastructure Analyst with strong analytical and problem solving skills. Reporting to the Manager, IT Support the successful incumbent will provide technology infrastructure operational and technical support to other staff, by providing specialized assistance with the evaluation, deployment and support of management information technology systems in MPAC.


RESPONSIBILITIES:

Provide front line technical support to MPAC staff regarding technology infrastructure and service delivery for a robust and resilient technology infrastructure;
Provide direct customer service support in technology infrastructure troubleshooting and resolution, through in-depth technical expertise to ensure that infrastructure is functional at all times;
Maintain systems and data security through the implementation of processes and procedures and on-going monitoring of staff adherence to the standards and procedures to ensure a secure technology environment;
Participate in Information Technology Service Management (ITSM) process meetings such as technical planning, technical review and Change Advisory Board meetings;
Conform to MPAC’s change/configuration management policies and procedures, and support technology infrastructure in the following domains:
Provide 1st level support for front line service staff in the daily use of technology and systems delivered on both Windows/Mac and IOS/Android Operating System platforms;Provide core Business Applications support to maximize client satisfaction;
Assist in application installation, including coordination of internal and external resources involved in application deployment;
Work remotely from direct management; provide remote Service Desk functions; and support front line staff in the daily use of technology and the systems delivered;
Assist with installation and management of network print/scan/fax services; and
Support the Audio/Visual and Conferencing solutions utilized in the corporation.
Travel will be required to provide support to surrounding MPAC Regional offices


LOCATION: Assessment Office #23 London, Ontario


QUALIFICATIONS:

Post-secondary education in computer science/technology support or related field, completed or in progress;
Minimum 3 years progressively responsible experience providing technical support to clients and/or end-users in at least one or more of the above domain areas, or a combination of experience and education;
Strong understanding of all aspects of the IT Infrastructure support area;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to troubleshoot operating systems;
Demonstrated understanding of data processing concepts/procedures and Internet and Intranet protocols;
Excellent customer service skills, including strong communication and interpersonal skills to build effective working relationships with clients and information technology colleagues at all levels in the organization;
Ability to work both independently and as part of a team, with the willingness to share ideas and solutions to technology challenges; and
Ability to multi-task and manage competing priorities, coupled with the ability to perform duties off hours and on an on-call basis as required.


